title.narrative: QUALITY INTEGRATED MCH INTERVENTIONS, INCLUDING IMMUNIZATION, NUTRITION SERVICES

description.narrative: By 2022, MOH and selected regional health care authorities and professionals, including conflict-affected districts, have increased capacity to provide quality integrated MCH services, including immunization and nutrition services., which contributes to Adolescent Health And Nutrition, Child Health, Child Health (Covid), Early Childhood Development, Early Childhood Development (Covid), Immunization, Immunization (Covid), Maternal And Newborn Health, Maternal And Newborn Health (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2022, all children and pregnant women in Ukraine, including in situations of humanitarian crisis, utilize improved quality and affordable mother and child health-care services.

title.narrative: By 2022, MOH and selected regional health care authorities and professionals, including conflict-affected districts, have increased capacity to provide quality integrated MCH services, including immunization and nutrition services.

description.narrative: In 2019 UNICEF provided increased support to MCH services, in particular related to immunization and mother and child care in the context of health reform through capacity development of health workers and managers, and targeted interventions for most vulnerable mothers and children in conflict affected areas. In addition to that, UNICEF continued its activities in the conflict-affected areas with technical assistance and support through the adoption and implementation of the universal-progressive patronage model and systemic strengthening at the primary health care level, bridging gaps in quality of provided services through a multi-sectorial approach. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:20/01/2020
